  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) achieved below required level due to single test condition, offset rationale documented. Operating envelope declared with concrete geometric and load bounds; applicability constraint scopes the domain to non-cannulated titanium alloy screws in ASTM F1717 fixtures only.",
